commit_message:
Do not copy /sbin/ip to /usr/bin/monasa-agent-ip

This patch removes the code that does the copy of /sbin/ip to
/usr/bin/monasca-agent-ip. There is a limitation with /sbin/ip
that limits copying it to a new name that is longer than
2 characters. The error is:

./monasca-agent-ip a
Object "nasca-agent-ip" is unknown, try "ip help".

As this is not working on RHEL,SLES, or Ubuntu this code
should be removed.

subject: Revert shebang fix in check-run-nova-compute↲
commit_message:
Revert shebang fix in check-run-nova-compute↲

In I3606c356a2103ce1e26e78e1192f0713b51e1ca4 we (again) moved to using
env to detect python versions. The problem with this is that this script
gets exec'ed:

      + exec /var/lib/nova/instanceha/check-run-nova-compute
      Running command: '/var/lib/nova/instanceha/check-run-nova-compute '
      /usr/bin/env: python -utt: No such file or directory

Revert the change for this script.
Hopefully once nova is able to do this on its own we can remove this
hack.

Closes-Bug: #1785245

subject: Add disruption detector for Overcloud endpoint monitoring
commit_message:
Add disruption detector for Overcloud endpoint monitoring

This adds a disruption detector python script that hooks
into the Overcloud controller haproxy to determine when
services go down. You can use this role to determine if
any given action disrupts the overcloud services uptime.

example usage:

- name: Check if overcloud services are disrupted
  hosts: <host for test action>:controller
  roles:
    - disruption-detector
    - <role to test for disruption>

subject: Spawn long-running processes in the driver agent
commit_message:
Spawn long-running processes in the driver agent

The OVN Octavia provider driver in the OvnProviderHelper
class caches these attributes:

    ovn_nbdb_api_for_events
    ovn_nb_idl_for_events
    ovn_nbdb_api

to not re-create things each time OVN IDL that is used for
handling events is called.

We should be using the Octavia Driver Provider Agent framework
instead to not have those long-running IDLs in the API process.

This change:
- Creates driver provider agent and registers its entry point
- While setting up the driver agent instance, start IDL that
  will handle events
- Stop caching ovn_nbdb_api, ovn_nb_idl_for_events and
  ovn_nbdb_api_for_events in the OvnProviderHelper class

Conflicts:

Fix revert snapshot issue

While there is a related fcmap stays in 100% copying clone state,
and this volume act as target volume in fcmap relationship,
revert snapshot will fail. This fix will stop 100% copying clone
fcmap, then let revert snapshot go.

Closes-bug: #1863070

subject: Handle empty config files
commit_message:
Handle empty config files

Current code was assuming if a reno.yaml file was found that it could
load that file to read config options. While probably a safe assumption
in the majority of cases, someone that isn't aware of this could modify
their config file to remove settings, leaving an empty or comment-only
file that when read does not actually load any yaml that can be used.

This adds protection for that to make reno does not try to use an empty
file.

Change-Id: I0ae0bcc93a79bbf66735833b654964b494485ee1
Signed-off-by: Sean McGinnis <sean.mcginnis@gmail.com>

subject: Call row.verify() when updating map columns with db_set
commit_message:
Call row.verify() when updating map columns with db_set

The verify() method will ensure that if the row's column in the db
has changed since we set it, that we will be notified and try the
transaction again with new values. This is important when we do a
read-update operation like we do for map columns in db_set. Since
we read the values add a few keys, then overwrite the whole value,
it is important that we don't do that if we have stale data.

Since ovs 2.6, there has been a setkey() operation that would
allow modifying a map w/o overwriting the whole value, but there
is a bug where it doesn't handle maps that have a refTable value
like Qos.queues. So using that before it is fixed [1] and all
packages have picked it up would cause breakage.

[1] https://patchwork.ozlabs.org/patch/1254735/

Closes-bug: #1867652
Change-Id: Ic898cefb4ced76e9e169b9f5d6caaace600abb0c
(cherry picked from commit b92d8742bf3f5e436bcb9160618b343e3c4595fa)
(cherry picked from commit 5fec1d724461e24206e2c1f66ad6ba8e342d4879)

subject: Bump default tox env from py37 to py38
commit_message:
Bump default tox env from py37 to py38

Python 3.8 is now our highest level supported python runtime.
This updates the default tox target environments to swap out
py37 for py38 to make sure local development testing is
covering this version.

This does not impact zuul jobs in any way, nor prevent local
tests against py37. It just changes the default if none is
explicitly provided.

subject: Don't break UEFI install with older IPAs
commit_message:
Don't break UEFI install with older IPAs

For Software RAID, we need to pass the boot mode to the IPA via a new
parameter. In case the IPA does not understand this new parameter yet,
we catch the error and fail for UEFI. This patch proposes to only fail
in the case of software RAID, since the older IPA can handle the general
case of UEFIi, e.g. with a whole disk image.

Change-Id: Id6b51dd19e83d20dc8d6d312cbec12d09bfd76c1

subject: Add ignore_errors in the ir plugin playbook
commit_message:
Add ignore_errors in the ir plugin playbook

Plugin's main playbook must continue in execution, no matter what,
so the whole playbook should ignore errors.

More background info: not all tasks of the role are ignoring errors,
which has caused an issue in the situation when the networking got
broken suddenly and ansible lost connection to the nodes while executing
the role -> after the connection got lost, tasks started failing and when
one of the tasks not ignoring errors failed, the whole playbook failed
which resulted in not calling the other half of the plugin's playbook,
which is responsible for publishing ...

Anyway, the role is supposed to gather as much as possible, so no matter
errors, all the tasks within it should be executed.

The patch adds ignore_errors in ir plugin's playbook, which shields
ir plugin from any errors and provides execution of all the tasks when
running the as infrared plugin.

Change-Id: Ib70a4b72fbed2eda730eb279e175107846fffeec

commit_message:
Fix multiple issues

Multiple issues combined to pass CI

1. drop tripleo-common-tempest-plugin

This is not needed plugin without any branches or releases. And wants Python 3
while we have Py2 for CentOS 7.

Original Change-Id: I9cab91b82941ea125b16d19e68722ce41a1f11f2
14:41 < hrw> is  tripleo-common-tempest-plugin your stuff?
14:43 <@EmilienM> yes and it does nothing. I thought we removed that?
14:43 <@EmilienM> apparently it's still here https://github.com/openstack/tripleo-common-tempest-plugin
14:43 <@EmilienM> we should burn it, weshay|ruck ^
14:44 < hrw> EmilienM: also fine to drop from train?
14:44 <@EmilienM> burn it everywhere you can
14:44 < hrw> THANKS
14:44 <@EmilienM> it has never been useful
14:44 <@EmilienM> and people who started it left
14:48 <@weshay|ruck> EmilienM, yup

2. Sensu: Remove ceph and process-checks plugins from client

The sensu image became unbuildable, failing to install the ceph plugin:

    Unable to resolve dependencies: sensu-plugins-ceph requires english (= 0.6.3)

This has happened because the author of the 'english' gem has seen fit
to publish a new 0.7.0 release, and 'yank' [1] all previous releases
from rubygems.

This change removes the ceph and process-checks plugins, which both
suffer from a dependency on the yanked english 0.6.3.

[1] https://rubygems.org/gems/english/versions/0.6.3

Original Change-Id: I9d34413fa10b5a2920aca60b08141bfaddcc7415
Closes-Bug: #1871600
(cherry picked from commit 818dc4d6ff12a3119be072e0c68e2d2c8da9b799)
(cherry picked from commit 2d1017be3fd658011fc5a86bd38b7265da306ea3)

3. Use freezer queens releases

There are no freezer releases in Rocky, so these packages stayed on
master. This is now python 3 only, so fails to build. Pin to Queens
6.0.0 releases.

4. Pin elasticsearch gem to <7.6.0 in fluentd

Since the release of the elasticsearch 7.6.0 gem, the fluentd image
fails to build on Ubuntu due to a transitive dependency on faraday.

ERROR:  Error installing fluent-plugin-elasticsearch:
    faraday requires Ruby version >= 2.3.

Pin elasticsearch to <7.6.0.

subject: [NetApp] Fix driver to honor standard extra specs
commit_message:
[NetApp] Fix driver to honor standard extra specs

During migration and manage/unmanage operations, if we used standard
extra_specs format (e.g. 'thin_provisioning'='True') instead of
NetApp based extra_specs format (e.g. 'netapp:thin_provisioned'='True'),
NetApp driver used to ignore these standard extra_specs settings
and continued the operation with the default option.
The driver is now fixed to handle this issue by honouring the
standard extra_specs during migration and manage/unmanage.

Change-Id: I48f4d966201fc8d6bd6eec0c37f1575b434310e7
Closes-Bug: #1707084
(cherry picked from commit 9250e02b56fa4a0d93fe4c32cdfac4eceab8d095)

subject: Improve VLAN allocations synchronization
commit_message:
Improve VLAN allocations synchronization

In order to reduce the number of elements retrieved from the DB, this
patch, before processing the VLAN allocations per physical network,
deleted those registers belonging to any unconfigured physical network.

The VLAN registers per physical network are deleted using a bulk delete
operation, to speed up the process.

Those missing VLAN registers per network are now created using a bulk
insert operation, available in the ORM. This bulk operation speeds up
the sync process.

commit_message:
Retry after hitting libvirt error VIR_ERR_OPERATION_INVALID in live migration.

To avoid rare condition such as while live migration job is still
running, qemu-kvm is killed accidentally, and nova thinks the job
is done, then post live migration starts to clean instance files,
this patch proposes such changes:

1.Do not treat VIR_ERR_OPERATION_INVALID as migration job completed.
2.`Pretend` the migration job is still running after hitting
  VIR_ERR_OPERATION_INVALID by returning VIR_DOMAIN_JOB_UNBOUNDED for
  a few times.
3.Number of retries can be configured by CONF.job_info_retry_count.

subject: Allow overriding template labels on create
commit_message:
Allow overriding template labels on create

Allow overriding cluster template labels at cluster creation time. This
is done using a prefix '++' on the label name. As an example for
override:
openstack coe cluster template create ... \
    --labels label1=value1,label2=value2
openstack coe cluster create ... \
    --labels ++label1=value111,++label3=value3

In this example we override an existing value (label1), add a new label
not on the original template list (label3) and take the value of the
original template label (label2).

The previous behavior where no prefix '++' is given for any of the
labels is kept, with cluster labels taking over all labels from the
template.

One assumption is that if one value is overriden, then all values not
overriden are taken from the template. We could trigger an error if
necessary for something like:
openstack coe cluster create --labels ++label1=value111,label2=value2
( not no prefix ++ on label2 )

or simply document this behavior.

Change-Id: I933942372c69614b8c80eee6f56444f1d6152a98
Task: 22202
Story: 2002591

subject: Remove six and python 2.7 full support
commit_message:
Remove six and python 2.7 full support

Six is in use to help us to keep support for python 2.7.
Since the ussuri cycle we decide to remove the python 2.7
support so we can go ahead and also remove six usage from
the python code.

Review process and help
-----------------------
Removing six introduce a lot of changes and an huge amount of modified files
To simplify reviews we decided to split changes into several patches to avoid
painful reviews and avoid mistakes.

To review this patch you can use the six documentation [1] to obtain help and
understand choices.

Additional informations
-----------------------
Changes related to 'six.b(data)' [2]
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

six.b [2] encode the given datas in latin-1 in python3 so I did the same
things in this patch.

Latin-1 is equal to iso-8859-1 [3].

This encoding is the default encoding [4] of certain descriptive HTTP
headers.

I suggest to keep latin-1 for the moment and to move to another encoding
in a follow-up patch if needed to move to most powerful encoding (utf8).

HTML4 support utf8 charset and utf8 is the default charset for HTML5 [5].

Note that this commit message is autogenerated and not necesserly contains
changes related to 'six.b'

[1] https://six.readthedocs.io/
[2] https://six.readthedocs.io/#six.b
[3] https://docs.python.org/3/library/codecs.html#standard-encodings
[4] https://www.w3schools.com/charsets/ref_html_8859.asp
[5] https://www.w3schools.com/html/html_charset.asp

Patch 13 of a serie of 28 patches

Change-Id: I09aa3b7ddd93087c3f92c76c893c609cb9473842

subject: [doc] tell to prefix ipv6 hosts with inet6
commit_message:
[doc] tell to prefix ipv6 hosts with inet6

Some environments with ipv6 used to connect with memcached servers
faced issues by omitting to prefix the host with the address family to
use.

Indeed libraries like python-memcached waiting for a prefix to
initialize the socket with the right address family. If the prefix
isn't given and that the host refer or bind an ipv6 then the socket
is initialized with an address family which correspond to an IPv4
and the connection doesn't work properly.

Openstack's puppet libraries already fixed that by introducing new
feature to automatically prefix the address if needed [1][2].

Anyway it could be worth to add more documentation on oslo.cache
to give more information to customers and avoid similar issues. These
changes aim to provide this documentation.

[1] https://review.opendev.org/#/q/status:merged+branch:master+topic:memcached-inet6-prefix
[2] https://review.opendev.org/#/c/661136/

Change-Id: I5e0b4818300348efe4625500792d9161281ed45a

commit_message:
Stop configuring install_command in tox.

Currently, we are overriding 'install_command' to use 'pip'. This is
considered poor behavior and 'python -m pip' should be used instead:

https://snarky.ca/why-you-should-use-python-m-pip/

It turns out that this is the the default value provided by tox:

https://tox.readthedocs.io/en/latest/config.html#conf-install_command

So we can remove the line and simply use the default value.

openstack-discuss thread
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-discuss/2020-April/014237.html

Replace six.iteritems() with .items()

six.iteritems to achieve iterators.

iterators in PY3 as well. And dict.items/keys will more readable.

[2] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-June/066391.html

subject: Set Neutron's l3_ha flag to True in standalone ML2/OVS job
commit_message:
Set Neutron's l3_ha flag to True in standalone ML2/OVS job

Even if this is standalone job, when l3_ha config option is set
to True in Neutron server, all routers will be created as HA
routers.
So for each such router created during the tests things like
keepalived, neutron-keepalived-state-change-monitor will be spawned
and also HA network will be created for tenants used by Tempest.
This will give us better coverage of things which are most commonly
used in Neutron.

Change-Id: I44ed60e88723e58ff1bb7bd0559540a596442f5a
(cherry picked from commit c53f747b1a96e696a44d6962e7624f49640e6a61)

subject: Stop configuring install_command in tox.
commit_message:
Stop configuring install_command in tox.

Currently, we are overriding 'install_command' to use 'pip'. This is
considered poor behavior and 'python -m pip' should be used instead:

https://snarky.ca/why-you-should-use-python-m-pip/

It turns out that this is the the default value provided by tox:

https://tox.readthedocs.io/en/latest/config.html#conf-install_command

So we can remove the line and simply use the default value.

openstack-discuss thread
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-discuss/2020-April/014237.html

Bumping pbr since oslo.log requires 3.1.1

Change-Id: I1f968c724e79e04bbc2fe8cb26fd54404b0350e0

In "ip_lib.ensure_device_is_ready", before retrieving the interface

subject: Improve VLAN allocations synchronization
commit_message:
Improve VLAN allocations synchronization

In order to reduce the number of elements retrieved from the DB, this
patch, before processing the VLAN allocations per physical network,
deleted those registers belonging to any unconfigured physical network.

The VLAN registers per physical network are deleted using a bulk delete
operation, to speed up the process.

Those missing VLAN registers per network are now created using a bulk
insert operation, available in the ORM. This bulk operation speeds up
the sync process.

Conflicts:
      neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/type_vlan.py

Change-Id: I8568e2277e157754aaff87a059a40e34e6a43e2b
Partial-Bug: #1862178
(cherry picked from commit 016e7826f165e69c3956375fc3aa8b8d642c9dc9)

(cherry picked from commit 8a6521e4457acbd7ceed941f363ee7c9872422ba)
